The paper deals with the construction and analysis of binary periodic sequences, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of Euler quotients and the condition $p$ divides $q-1$ suggests a connection to number theory (cs.NT). The determination of minimal polynomials and linear complexities involves algebraic and computational techniques, which are relevant to computer science (cs.CC) and discrete mathematics (cs.DS).
